e player to make a wish, but if he words himself badly (or I simply don't think he should get his wish fulfilled), it can go horribly awry. For example, the wish &quot;I wish I could stay this happy for the rest of my life&quot; may result in immediate death, or &quot;I wish for a horde of summoned monsters to assist me in my battle&quot; may result in 30 bunnies appearing out of nowhere to attack the opponents. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uglipthegnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glip the Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pantsless Asst. Administrator</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/17/02 12:03:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.keithparkinson.com/glip2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: spells,  got to love them.</span><hr size=1> Wall of Force and Wall of Iron<br><br>Wall of Force summons a big indestructable wall (or sphere) proportional to your level which is transparent and Wall of Iron just brings a big iron wall proportional to your level.<br><br>You can do so much awesome things with those spells.<br><br><br>Other than that - <br>Cantrip is extremely fun to mess around with and any of the higher Phantasmal forces (illusion spells) are a blast too. <p><b><a href=mailto:Glip@thesafehouse.org><font size="5">Glip the Gnome</font></a></b><br>Best Smelling Admin: <a href=http://www.thesafehouse.org>The Safehouse</a><br>Overlord of Doom: <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthescurvydogbuffet>The Scurvy Dog Buffet</a><br><font color="gray" size="4"